post.description:
Apply Alteon Config

Example curl:
```bash
curl -k -H "Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46MXFhejJ3c3gzZWRj" https://10.101.101.4/config?action=apply
```

get.description:
Apply Alteon apply status

Example curl:
```bash
curl -k -H "Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46MXFhejJ3c3gzZWRj" https://10.101.101.4/monitor?prop=agApplyPending
```

ok.description: agApplyPending : 2 or 3  value 2 means apply is required value 3 means no apply is requierd

put.summary: Apply Alteon apply process check method used !!!!GET!!!,Because same get method can not writing in swagger API Doc .
put.description:
Apply Alteon apply process check

Example curl:
```bash
curl -k -H "Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46MXFhejJ3c3gzZWRj" https://10.101.101.4/config?prop=agApplyConfig
```

ok.description: agApplyConfig : 1 or 3 or 4 or 5 or 6   value 1 means no apply is in process, idle status. value 3  means the apply is in progress. value 4 means the apply is completed successfully value 5 means the apply process failed. value 6 means the apply is completed successfully, with a warning

post.description:
Save Alteon Config

Example curl:
```bash
curl -k -H "Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46MXFhejJ3c3gzZWRj" https://10.101.101.4/config?action=save
```

get.description:
Save Alteon config process check

Example curl:
```bash
curl -k -H "Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46MXFhejJ3c3gzZWRj" https://10.101.101.4/config?prop=agSaveConfig
```

ok.description: agSaveConfig : 1 or 2 or 3 or 4 or 5  value 1 means save to flash memory value 2 means idle no save operation in progress value 3  inprogress the save operation is in progress value 4 is complete the last save operation completed. value 5 faild the last save operation failed

VirtServerIpAddress.description: IP address of the virtual server.

VirtServerState.description: Enable or disable the virtual server. Values: 2=enabled, 3=disabled.

VirtServerWeight.description: The virtual server Global SLB weight.

VirtServerVname.description: The name of the virtual server.

VirtPort.description: The layer4 virtual port number of the service. It can be either 1 for IP or between 9 to 65534. Virt port numbers 2 to 9 are invalid.

RealPort.description: The layer4 real port number of the service. It can be either 0 for multiple real ports or 1 for IP service or between 5 to 65534. Ports 2 to 5 are invalid.

ConnmgtStatus.description: Connection management configuration for HTTP traffic (enable/disable/pooling) [default: disable]

ConnmgtTimeout.description: Connection management server side connection idle timeout in minutes [0-32768] [default: 10]

SSLpol.description: SSL policy name associated with this virtual service. Set none to delete entry

ServCert.description: Server certificate name associated with this virtual service

XForwardedFor.description: Enable/disable X-Forwarded-For for proxy mode. Values: 1=enabled, 2=disabled,

HttpRedir.description: Enable/disable HTTP/HTTPS redirect for GSLB. Values: 1=enabled, 2=disabled, 2147483647=unsupported.

AppwallWebappId.description: This object ID allows configuring the web security ID.

Http2.description: Http2 policy name associated with this virtual service.

AddServer.description: The real server to be added to the group.

RemoveServer.description: The real server to be removed from the group.

Name.description: The name of the real server group.

HealthID.description: NoCheck or http or https or tcp

FQDN.description: The Fqdn field of the server.

IpVers.description: The type of IP address. Values: 1=ipv4, 2=ipv6, 2147483647=unsupported.

State.description: Enable or disable the server. Values: 2=enabled, 3=disabled

service_http_s_fastview.description: Service HTTP FASTVIEW (does not exist in SA).
